    answer: 2,
    explanation: "Information rights management (IRM) Certificates are central to authentication, encryption, and trust management in cloud environments. IRM relies on certificate services to bind usage rights to documents and to manage who can access or modify them, making the issuing and revocation of certificates an essential function. DLP focuses on monitoring and controlling the movement of sensitive data, but it does not involve certificate issuance. TEE provides isolated execution for secure computing; it does not manage certificates. SIEM aggregates and analyzes logs for threat detection and compliance. The Official xmexam.taobao.com xmexam.taobao.com",
