    answer: 0,
    explanation: "BCP A business continuity plan (BCP) sustains operations during a disruptive event, such as a natural disaster or network outage. It can also be called a continuity of operations plan (COOP). A disaster recovery plan (DRP) works to restore the organization to normal operations after such an event has occurred. The decision of what needs to be included in a business continuity plan is determined by a business impact assessment (BIA), which determines what is necessary for the business to function vs. “nice to have.\" An incident response team (IRT) responds when an incident is declared. The Official",
