    id: 687,
    text: "How do CSPs separate tenants in a cloud computing environment?",
    options: ["By", "applying encryption By housing tenants in separate racks", "By using logical design", "By housing tenants in separate facilities"],
    answer: 2,
    explanation: "By using logical design Proper separation of tenants prevents data leakage or unauthorized access by different customers on the same infrastructure. CSPs rely on virtualization and logical isolation techniques to keep tenant environments separate. This approach allows multiple tenants to securely share the same physical infrastructure without interference. Housing tenants in separate racks describes co-location rather than a cloud computing environment. Housing tenants in separate facilities does not describe a cloud computing environment. Applying encryption can protect data confidentiality, but it does not provide structural isolation between tenants. The Official",
