    explanation: "Having two locations in separate areas of the data center where two or more ISPs can connect Resilient, multi-vendor network pathways reduce the risk of outages and ensure availability, which is a core principle of cloud service reliability. Having two locations in separate areas of the data center where two or more ISPs can connect ensures physical and vendor diversity by providing multiple independent entry points and protects against single points of failure. Securing one primary entryway creates a single point of failure. Relying on cellular data connectivity to connect to multiple ISPs lacks scalability. Using satellite links as a backup can introduce latency and weather-related reliability issues. 198. The Official",
