    explanation: "The temperature is ideal, but the humidity level is too low It's very important to ensure that both temperature and humidity levels are ideal within a data center. The American Society of Heating, Refrigeration, and Air Conditioning Engineers (ASHRAE) recommend that data centers have a temperature between 64.4-80.6 degrees Fahrenheit/18-27 degrees Celcius and a humidity level between 40-60 percent relative humidity. A humidity level of 35 percent is too low and could lead to an excess of electrostatic discharge. The Official",
