    id: 735,
    text: "Which of the following components is considered a compute resource?",
    options: ["Virtual machine", "Hypervisor", "Operating", "system Security group"],
    answer: 0,
    explanation: "Virtual machine Compute resources are the components that provide the capability to run workloads and applications. A virtual machine provides processing capability, memory, and storage for running applications, making it a primary example of a compute resource in cloud computing. A hypervisor is the software layer that manages virtual machines, not the compute resource itself. An operating system is software that runs on compute resources but is not itself the resource. A security group is a network security control used to manage inbound and outbound traffic, not a compute resource.The Official Practical Cloud Security: A Guide for Secure Design and Deployment, 2nd Edition (ISBN: 978-1098148171). Pg 17.",
