    answer: 0,
    explanation: "Database activity monitoring (DAM) tool Insider and post-breach threats can target databases directly, and organizations must deploy supplementary security controls to monitor and block malicious queries. A DAM tool monitors database queries in real time, logs activity, and can block suspicious SQL commands before they cause damage or exfiltration. An XML firewall secures SOAP and XML message traffic, not SQL queries. An API gateway focuses on securing REST and JSON-based API traffic, not database-level activity. A WAF can block HTTP/HTTPS traffic to stop SQL injection attempts at the application layer, but it does not provide continuous, direct monitoring of database queries needed once attackers are inside the network. The Official",
