    id: 879,
    text: "A bad actor is targeting a cloud web application. They were able to send a properly formatted SELECT statement through one of the input fields. This returned data about the database that they could use to further attack the application. What is the name of this type of attack?",
    options: ["Injection attack", "SQL", "reflection", "XSS CSRF"],
    answer: 0,
    explanation: "Injection attack An injection attack occurs when an attacker can send a properly formatted command to compromise a system. In this case, the attacker used a SQL injection attack with a SELECT statement through one of the input fields in the web application. This malicious query can return information about the database that should not be publicly available. To prevent injection attacks, it's important to ensure that any data sent through an input field is properly sanitized and validated. Cross-site scripting (XSS) is an attack against the user's browser and the user's trust in the website. There are three types of XSS: DOM, Reflected, and Stored. Cross-site request forgery (CSRF) tricks the user into performing actions they would not have otherwise. It abuses the trust the server has in the user. SQL reflection is not a standard type of attack. The Official Practical Cloud Security: A Guide for Secure Design and Deployment, 2nd Edition. Pg 96. xmexam.taobao.com",
