    explanation: "Abuse case Attackers often exploit unhandled or poorly validated inputs to compromise applications or systems. Abuse case testing focuses on deliberately sending invalid, unexpected, or malicious data to determine whether the system can handle these inputs without failing or exposing vulnerabilities. Dynamic testing refers broadly to evaluating software while it is running, not specifically to testing unexpected inputs. Whitebox refers to testing with full knowledge of internal code and structure. Static testing analyzes code or documentation without executing the program. The Official",
