    explanation: "Federated Identity Management Federated Identity Management (FIM) allows this scenario to work well, especially when the university that knows the scientists does the authentication by acting as the identity provider. Each university (if, that is, where each scientist works) can authenticate those they know, such as their students or employees. They become the identity provider in a FIM setup. Open Authorization ( OAuth) is used for the authorization piece of IAAA (Identification Authentication Authorization Accounting). It is not used for authentication. It can be used with OpenID for that purpose though. Kerberos is a single sign-on that has been used widely since it was developed in the late 1980s. In a way, it is similar to technologies that enable FIM, such as OAuth and SAML. Active Directory is a tool used within a corporation for authentication. It can be connected using Azure Active Directrory to FIM for cloud-based services though. The Official",
