    explanation: "Rollback process Proper release management ensures stability and minimizes risks during updates. A rollback process provides a predefined plan to return systems to their previous stable state if a release introduces issues. Automated testing helps prevent issues before release, but it does not allow reversion after problems occur. A post-implementation review happens after deployment and evaluates outcomes rather than actively reversing changes. Manual scheduling determines when releases occur, but it does not undo a problematic release. The Official",
