    explanation: "VLAN In cloud security, isolation is critical because it limits lateral movement by attackers and enforces logical separation of workloads. A VLAN (virtual local area network) allows administrators to logically segment a physical network into separate broadcast domains, isolating hosts without requiring separate physical switches. DHCP assigns IP addresses to devices but does not isolate them. DNSSEC secures DNS queries and responses from tampering but has no role in host isolation. A VPN provides secure remote connectivity, not internal segmentation of hosts.Practical Cloud Security: A Guide for Secure Design and Deployment, 2nd Edition (ISBN: 978-1098148171). Pg 140. The Official",
