    explanation: "Immutable architecture Immutable means unchanging over time or unable to be changed. Immutability of cloud infrastructure is a preferred state. It is feasible to easily decommission all virtual infrastructure components utilized by an older version of software and deploy a new virtual infrastructure in cloud settings. Immutable infrastructure is a solution to the problem of systems deviating from baseline settings over time. This is using a golden image to start virtual machines. IaC is a virtual environment. The infrastructure is no longer physical routers, switches, and servers; it is now virtual routers, switches, and servers. That could also be called a virtual architecture, although IaC is the common language today. Blockchain technology has an immutable element. It is, or should be, impossible to alter the record of who it belonged to, such as what we have with cryptocurrency. The FBI has been able to recover stolen bitcoins and return them to the rightful owner.The Official",
