    answer: 1,
    explanation: "International Standards Organization/International Electrotechnical Commission (ISO/IEC) 27018 ISO/IEC 27018 is a standard for providing security and privacy within cloud computing. The ISO/IEC 27018 focuses on five key principles, which include communication (relaying information to cloud customers), consent (receiving permission before using customer data for any reason), control (cloud customers retain full control over their own data in the cloud), transparency (cloud providers inform customers of any potential exposure to support staff and contractors), and independent and yearly audits (cloud providers must undergo yearly audits performed by a third party). ISO/IEC 27001 is information security, cybersecurity, and privacy protection - Information Security Management System (ISMS). This is good for building and auditing a corporation's ISMS. ISO/IEC 27050 is information technology - electronic discovery (e-discovery). ISO/IEC 31000 is risk management guidelines. The Official",
