    explanation: "Termination The termination section of a contract specifies the conditions under which the agreement can be ended, including requirements for advance notice, penalties, and obligations that must be met before early termination. This ensures both parties understand their rights and obligations, helping prevent disputes or unexpected service interruptions. Assurance refers to commitments regarding service quality or compliance. Right to audit details how a customer can review a provider’s controls and practices. The metrics section defines performance measurements or service levels. The Official",
