    answer: 0,
    explanation: "By referring to the CSP's SOC reports In cloud security, customers do not have direct access to a provider’s internal systems, so they rely on third-party assurances to understand the effectiveness of security controls. System and Organization Controls (SOC) reports provide independent assessments of a CSP’s controls, allowing customers to gain assurance without having direct access to their internal systems. Customers cannot audit a CSP’s internal systems directly unless the provider allows it, so hiring external auditors is not a practical method for assurance. Internal audits of the customer’s own environment do not provide insight into the CSP’s security controls. Most CSPs do not allow customers to perform penetration tests on shared systems. The Official xmexam.taobao.com",
