    answer: 1,
    explanation: "Mean time to detect (MTTD) MTTD measures the average time it takes for an organization to identify a potential security incident after it occurs. A lower MTTD indicates that monitoring and detection systems, such as SIEMs or IDS/IPS, are effective at identifying threats quickly. MTTR measures the time taken to fully remediate an incident. Time to deploy patches measures how quickly updates are applied. Intrusion attempts counts how the number of attacks that have been attempted, but it does not measure how long detection takes.The Official",
