    id: 1458,
    text: "Under the European Union (EU) General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), who determines the purpose and means related to the processing of personal data?",
    options: ["Data", "processor Data custodian", "Data controller", "Data owner"],
    answer: 2,
    explanation: "Data controller The data controller determines the purpose and means of processing personal data. Under GDPR, the data controller is defined as the entity or person who, alone or jointly with others, decides why and how personal data is processed. This includes responsibility for ensuring compliance with GDPR and addressing data subject rights. The data processor processes personal data on behalf of the controller, such as a third-party service provider. They act under the instructions of the data controller and are not responsible for defining the purpose or methods of processing. The data custodian manages and safeguards data but does not define its purpose or means of processing. Their role is operational, ensuring compliance with policies set by the controller. The data owner is responsible for classifying and setting access controls for data within an organization but does not have a legal definition under GDPR. The Official",
